# Standard-norm for big updates & ops recoveries (FROZEN)

Every **big update**, incident recovery, compensation, or pack/grant repair **must follow this standard-norm**. Do not invent a parallel shape.

## Compensation / recovery marker (required)

Use `accountCompensationsApplied` exactly like existing campaign/patrol comps:

| Rule | Standard |
|------|----------|
| Key length | **≤ 64 chars** (sanitize truncates — long `0x…` tx hashes break idempotency) |
| Value shape | **`{ amount, at }` only** |
| `amount` | Small applied marker or monball count — **not** large gold totals (sanitize clamps to monball limits) |
| Id style | Short stable ids, e.g. `patrol_extra50_2026-07-19`, `pack_gold_gp40k_<tx16>` |

**Forbidden:** stuffing full tx hashes, rich metadata objects, or gold quantities into compensation values. Put tx / gold / moneyBefore-after on the **purchase ledger** (`monex:purchases:user:…`) or ops notes instead.

## Pack purchase recoveries

1. Prove on-chain payment + bound wallet + package price.
2. Check purchase ledger / `monex:tx-used:` before crediting.
3. Credit **once** using a short compensation id; skip if already present.
4. Annotate ledger/`tx-used` with recovery details (not the compensation value).
5. Re-read save and confirm money/monballs match a **single** grant.

## Before every claim / pack mutation (client)

Call `MonExAuth.cancelPendingCloudSave()` so stale autosaves cannot overwrite the grant (same as release / battle / quest).

## Save PUT economy

Soft currencies are mutation-API authoritative for gains. Catastrophic drops on full-save PUT (stale mobile overwrite of a pack grant) must be blocked — see `MAX_SAVE_DROP` in `save-economy-guard.js`.

## Pre-merge check for big updates

- [ ] Compensation ids ≤ 64 and `{ amount, at }` only
- [ ] Idempotent if script/endpoint is re-run
- [ ] No second save system; apply server save after grants
- [ ] Stale autosave cannot undo the grant
- [ ] `npm test` in `cloudflare/monex-api` for touched libs

## One-line summary

**Short compensation keys, `{amount,at}` only, ledger holds the proof — never improvise a new recovery shape on a big update.**
